    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Slice your <strong>pork belly</strong> finely with a sharp knife</p><p>Rub your <strong>five-spice</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> all over the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>pork belly</strong> so that it's fully coated in spice</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/taiwanese-five-spice-braised-pork-belly-pak-choi-and-cauliflower-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid), over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> sliced pork belly</strong> and cook for 3 min on each side or until it's browned</p><p>Peel and finely slice (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>gluten free soy sauce</strong> and <strong>rice vinegar</strong> with 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[195ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> braising liquid</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/taiwanese-five-spice-braised-pork-belly-pak-choi-and-cauliflower-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once browned, add <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>sliced garlic </strong>to the <strong>pork belly</strong> and cook for 1 min further</p><p>Add your <strong>braising liquid</strong> and bring to the boil</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for 40-45 min or until the pork belly is tender</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/taiwanese-five-spice-braised-pork-belly-pak-choi-and-cauliflower-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the pork belly is cooking, peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Crush your <strong>roasted peanuts</strong> with a <strong>rolling pin</strong> (keep them in the bag so you don't lose them!)</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/taiwanese-five-spice-braised-pork-belly-pak-choi-and-cauliflower-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pork has been cooking for 30 min, add your <strong>white long grain rice </strong>and <strong>cauliflower rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 110ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[175ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[225ml]</span> cold water and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/taiwanese-five-spice-braised-pork-belly-pak-choi-and-cauliflower-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut the base from your <strong>pak choi</strong> and separate into leaves</p><p>Heat a separate large, wide-based pan or wok (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> pak choi</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until the pak choi is tender with a slight bite</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/taiwanese-five-spice-braised-pork-belly-pak-choi-and-cauliflower-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the pak choi is cooking, add your <strong>hoisin sauce</strong> to the <strong>pork belly</strong> and cook over a medium-high heat for 1-2 min or until thick and sticky \u2013 this is your <strong>Taiwanese five-spice</strong> <strong>braised pork belly</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/taiwanese-five-spice-braised-pork-belly-pak-choi-and-cauliflower-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Taiwanese five-spice</strong> <strong>braised pork belly</strong> over the <strong>cooked cauliflower</strong> <strong>rice </strong>with the<strong> pak choi</strong> to the side</p><p>Garnish with the<strong> crushed peanuts</strong> and <strong>chopped coriander</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
